<div class="main section">
	<div class="container">
		<h3>Customization</h3>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-md-12 sub-header">
						Initialize (Optional)
						<div class="code col-md-12 full-code">
								//Default Values <br>
								<br>
								$.skylo({ <br>
									&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'state': 'info', <br>
									&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'inchSpeed': 200, <br>
									&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'initialBurst': 5, <br>
									&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'flat': false <br>
								});
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>


		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-md-5 sub-header">
						state
						<div class="code">[ "info", "success", "warning", "danger" ]</div>
					</div>
					<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-1 sub-desc">
						Using Twitter Bootstrap default state, we can switch the theme of the loader.
					</div>
				</div>

			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-md-4 sub-header">
						inchSpeed
						<div class="code">[milliseconds]</div>
					</div>
					<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-2 sub-desc">
						The loader can inch forward to signify loading. Adjust the inch speed so that the inching can appear fast or slow.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
				<div class="row">
			      <div class="col-md-4 sub-header">
			        initialBurst
			        <div class="code">[0 - 100]</div>
			      </div>
			      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-2 sub-desc">
			        When we start the loader, we set a initial burst of loading so that it kicks off the impression that the loading have begin. Adjust how much initial burst that you wanted.
			      </div>
			    </div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
				<div class="row">
			      <div class="col-md-4 sub-header">
			        flat
			        <div class="code">[true/false]</div>
			      </div>
			      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-2 sub-desc">
			        If true, remove the animated striped UI of the progress bar.
			      </div>
			    </div>
			</div>
		</div>


	</div>
</div>

